Property.preferredName: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander Patient Demographics
Property.preferredDefinition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, Guam, Samoa, or other Pacific Islands. The term covers particularly people who identify themselves as part-Hawaiian, Native Hawaiian, Guamanian or Chamorro, Carolinian, Samoan, Chuukese (Trukese), Fijian, Kosraean, Melanesian, Micronesian, Northern Mariana Islander, Palauan, Papua New Guinean, Pohnpeian, Polynesian, Solomon Islander, Tahitian, Tokelauan, Tongan, Yapese, or Pacific Islander, not specified. The concept refers also to individuals who classify themselves as described below.:A person who requires medical care.:statistical characterization of human populations (or segments of human populations broken down by age or sex or income etc.).
